This article is a transcript of remarks made by President Trump on the South Lawn. He discusses his meeting with Pastor Brunson, who was recently released from Turkey, and thanks Turkey and President Erdogan. He also mentions his conversation with the King of Saudi Arabia regarding the disappearance of journalist Jamal Khashoggi, and says that Secretary of State Mike Pompeo will be traveling to Saudi Arabia to investigate the matter. President Trump mentions that the King denied any knowledge of what happened and suggested that it could have been rogue killers. He also expresses his changing feelings towards Turkey. The President dismisses Senator Elizabeth Warren's DNA test results and expresses his hope that she runs for president. He also comments on the bankruptcy of Sears and the arms deal with Saudi Arabia. The President ends by stating that North Korea is coming along well.